item.title: CVE-2020-29509|2024-09-17T03:43:39.703Z -- golang -- go
item.description: The encoding/xml package in Go (all versions) does not correctly preserve the semantics of attribute namespace prefixes during tokenization round-trips, which allows an attacker to craft inputs that behave in conflicting ways during different stages of processing in affected downstream applications.

item.title: CVE-2020-29511|2024-09-17T04:09:22.123Z -- golang -- go
item.description: The encoding/xml package in Go (all versions) does not correctly preserve the semantics of element namespace prefixes during tokenization round-trips, which allows an attacker to craft inputs that behave in conflicting ways during different stages of processing in affected downstream applications.
